{
  "stem": "13258.4",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And at which point, I had-- at the one repeated questions, we said-- when I-- what my nationality was.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Now, one must understand, to the Russians, nationality does not mean citizenship, but it means, really, ethnicity.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And that ethnicity, in Russia, is always listed in your identity card.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Once a Jew, once a Pole, once a-- whatever, Chinese, you are-- you and all your heirs are going to be the same.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Well, I stated-- we had stated when we had received our temporary Russian documents, that our ethnicity was Polish.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Going out from the idea that, if the war ends, if we say we are Jewish, religion hasn't been asked.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Ethnicity is being asked.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "If we say that we are Jewish, then when the war ends we have to stay there, even if there is a Poland.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "If we say we are Polish, we can go back to Poland.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So this way I got-- when I said that I go in the army, and I was told two days later to report, I didn't know yet what army I'm going to.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It wasn't until two days later, when I reported at 10 o'clock in the evening to that office, that the officer told me where to go, whom to find at the railroad station, and so on.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then finally, he said, and if somebody asks you where you are going, tell him you're going to the 1st Polish Kosciuszko Infantry Division.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And good luck, and behave yourself with dignity.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And off I went.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "On June 5th, after all kinds of manipulations, being in a collection point and put on a train and travelling-- on June 5th, we arrived at a railroad station not far from the town of [?",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Railzai ?], the city of-- the railroad station [?",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
